        <h2>Who we are</h2>q
      </header>
      <p>
        DesignWorks was formerly known as Promotional Student Designs, which was launched in the spring of 2013 as a graphic designer alliance for Northwestern University by Benedict Dungca and Arisa Toyosaki. It was created with the intention of raising aesthetic awareness on campus and meeting the communityâ€™s needs for a high-quality graphic design service. Met with beyond expected market demands, the team became profitable and decided to become a business after merging with an existing advertisement company, AdWorks. After a series of meetings between AdWorks and Promotional Student Designs, the two companies decided to merge and expand product offerings. With new capabilities and a new team, we revamped our name to DesignWorks.
      </p>
      <footer>
